Experience Senior Revenue Accountant Epocrates, Inc. March 2006  – Present (9 years 6 months) Daily Responsibilities: 
•	Review all revenue contracts and process orders to ensure all documentation is in compliance with revenue and company policy, to understand all billing provisions, and to prepare customer invoices and credit memos;  
•	Ensures BESP is properly allocated to all order deliverables and sales tax is properly calculated based on product taxability rules; 
•	Manages Fulfillment Events / Revenue Recognition for assigned Product Lines following the guidance of EITF 08-1, SOP 97-2, and SAB 104; 
•	Works closely with FP&A to resolve discrepancies in revenue actuals versus forecast and, in doing so, assists with forecasting revenue for future periods;  
•	Works with Sales Operations to assist in swap analysis, and to provide guidance on amendment processing and order entry issues within the ERP system; 
•	Assists with process narratives, implementation of identified controls and sample testing for SOX 404 preparation; 
•	Performs month-end reconciliation of Deferred Revenue and Revenue Accounts ensuring revenue deferrals are recorded properly and the recognition of Revenue occurs in the proper periods; 
Quarterly/Audit Responsibilities: 
•	Prepares quarterly PBC audit schedules, including but not limited to VSOE/BESP Analysis, Flux Analysis, Deferred Revenue Rollforward, Related Party analysis, credit memo analysis, and Linked order analysis in accordance with company bundling policy; 
